.TH "pnut" "1" "2026-04-10"
.P
.SH NAME
.P
pnut - lightweight, unprivileged Linux sandbox
.P
.SH SYNOPSIS
.P
\fBpnut\fR \fB--config\fR \fIpath\fR [\fB--\fR] [\fIcommand\fR [\fIargs.\&.\&.\&\fR]]
.P
.SH DESCRIPTION
.P
\fBpnut\fR confines processes using Linux kernel isolation
primitives.\& It requires no root privileges, no setuid binaries, and no special
capabilities.\& All isolation is bootstrapped from CLONE_NEWUSER, so any
unprivileged user can create a sandbox.\&
.P
The sandbox is configured entirely through a TOML file (see \fBpnut.\&toml\fR(5)).\&
The only runtime arguments are the config path and an optional command to
execute inside the sandbox.\&
.P
\fBpnut\fR supports two execution modes:
.P
\fBonce\fR
.RS 4
(default) Fork a child via \fBclone3\fR(2) with the requested namespaces.\& The
parent supervises the child and propagates its exit status.\&
.P
.RE
\fBexecve\fR
.RS 4
The calling process \fBunshare\fR(2)s into the new namespaces and then
\fBexecve\fR(2)s the command directly.\& No supervising parent is created.\&
.P
.RE
.SH OPTIONS
.P
\fB-c\fR, \fB--config\fR \fIpath\fR
.RS 4
Path to the TOML sandbox configuration file.\& Required.\&
.P
.RE
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
.RS 4
Print help and exit.\&
.P
.RE
\fB-V\fR, \fB--version\fR
.RS 4
Print version and exit.\&
.P
.RE
\fIcommand\fR [\fIargs.\&.\&.\&\fR]
.RS 4
Command and arguments to run inside the sandbox, specified after a \fB--\fR
separator.\& If provided, this overrides the \fB[run]\fR section in the
configuration file.\& Either a command on the command line or a \fB[run]\fR
section in the config is required.\&
.P
.RE
.SH CONFIGURATION
.P
All sandbox behavior is controlled by the TOML configuration file.\& See
\fBpnut.\&toml\fR(5) for the full schema reference.\&
.P
